Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
panCenter(25.10)                                              panCenter(25.10)

Name
       panCenter  - Pans in the viewable window to the center point defined by
       the specified coordinates

Syntax
       panCenter

        [-help]

       <x y>

       Pans in the viewable window to the center point defined by  the  speci-
       fied  coordinates.  Use this command at any stage of the design flow to
       view the design area around a specific point.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each panCenter parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man panCenter.

       <x y>  Specifies the x and y coordinates of the center point.

Example
       The following command pans the viewable  window  to  the  center  point
       (x=100, y=200)

       panCenter 100 200

